@page
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Tech Review Sprint";
}

<section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Tech Review Sprint</h1>
        <p>A fast, director-level assessment that turns “we think…” into a prioritized, evidence-based plan.</p>
        <p><strong>Best for:</strong> teams that need clarity on architecture, security, delivery, and cost—without starting a long engagement.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="outcomes">
    <div class="container">
        <h2>Outcomes (what you get)</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>A clear picture of what’s working, what’s risky, and what’s slowing you down</li>
            <li>A prioritized backlog of fixes and improvements (quick wins + strategic work)</li>
            <li>Practical guidance on security, reliability, performance, and cost</li>
            <li>A decision-ready view of where to invest next (and what to stop doing)</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="included">
    <div class="container">
        <h2>What’s included</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Lightweight discovery: goals, constraints, and current pain points</li>
            <li>
                Targeted reviews of:
                <ul>
                    <li>Architecture &amp; integration patterns</li>
                    <li>Cloud posture &amp; cost drivers</li>
                    <li>Delivery pipeline &amp; environments</li>
                    <li>Observability &amp; operational readiness</li>
                    <li>Security &amp; identity access patterns</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Stakeholder alignment checkpoints (to prevent surprises later)</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="how-it-works">
    <div class="container">
        <h2>How it works (simple + low-friction)</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Kickoff + context (what success looks like, current blockers)</li>
            <li>Rapid review (docs, repo scans where appropriate, environment walk-through)</li>
            <li>Findings workshop (validate assumptions, confirm priorities)</li>
            <li>Executive readout (final recommendations + next-step options)</li>
        </ol>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="deliverables">
    <div class="container">
        <h2>Typical deliverables</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Findings &amp; Recommendations (executive-friendly)</li>
            <li>Risk &amp; Opportunity Register (ranked by impact/effort)</li>
            <li>90-day action plan (sequenced and realistic)</li>
            <li>Optional: architecture diagram refresh + target-state sketch</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="ideal-situations">
    <div class="container">
        <h2>Ideal situations</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>“We’re moving fast but feel exposed.”</li>
            <li>“Our cloud costs are rising and we can’t explain why.”</li>
            <li>“Delivery is slow and releases feel risky.”</li>
            <li>“We inherited a system and need an expert baseline quickly.”</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="cta">
    <div class="container">
        <h2>Ready to get clarity quickly?</h2>
        <p><a href="/intake">Start here: Intake Form →</a></p>
    </div>
</section>
